# Collective DAO Starter Kit: copy to .env and set values.
# Only VITE_WC_PROJECT_ID is required for the DAO (wallet connection).
# Get a project ID from https://cloud.reown.com (Reown / WalletConnect).
# No other keys are required for this kit.
#
# Optional: Rootstock RPC API key (Mainnet or Testnet). In this browser starter kit,
# public nodes are preferred by default for local dev reliability.
# The key is still kept for environments where key-based RPC endpoints are allowed.
# Get a free key at https://dashboard.rpc.rootstock.io.
# Leave empty to use public fallbacks:
# - Mainnet: https://public-node.rsk.co
# - Testnet: https://public-node.testnet.rsk.co
#
# This kit does NOT use PRIVATE_KEY. Writes (stake, unstake, vote) are signed by the
# user's connected wallet (RainbowKit); the Collective SDK receives a WalletClient
# from Wagmi for each write. See README "How the starter kit uses the Collective SDK for writes".
#
# All VITE_* variables are bundled into the client at build time. Do not put secrets here.

VITE_WC_PROJECT_ID=''
VITE_ROOTSTOCK_RPC_API_KEY=''